    },
    "Management": {
      "text": "Depends on the age of the child and degree of displacement\nNon-Operative\nFor almost all children, will approach non-operatively\nExcellent remodeling ability of bone and ROM to shoulder\nOrtho consult is needed to determine the best approach\nSling and swathe splint\n, or\ncoaptation splint\nGentle ROM in 1-2 weeks as tolerated\nOperative Indications\nMore than 45 degrees of angulation\nLess than 50% apposition of proximal humerus and shaft\nOpen fractures\nNeurovascular injury\nIntraarticular fracture",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "Sling and swathe splint",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Sling_and_swathe_splint"
        },
        {
          "text": "coaptation splint",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Coaptation_splint"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Disposition": {
      "text": "Slightly displaced fracture: Sling and ortho follow up\nDisplaced >30 degrees: may need closed reduction",
